fields.name: intro_text
fields.value: A 4 day itinerary through Jordan where you combine visits to the highlights of Jordan - with camping with the Bedouins and visits to less known sites. Jordan from a different perspective!

fields.name: entry_point

fields.name: Highlights
fields.value: Madaba, Dead Sea, Karak, Dana, Petra, Wadi Rum and Mt Nebo

segments.title: QAIA - Madaba
segments.content:
Arrive at the airport and your driver will meet you in the arrivals hall holding a name sign and take you on a short ride (30mins) to Madaba. Your overnight stay is in Madaba. 


Option: If you arrive in the morning, you can head north to visit the beautiful Roman city of Jerash – one of the best preserved Roman ruins outside of Italy. the Hippodrome, colonnaded way, theatre and temple of Artemis are some of the highlights.

elements.subTitle: Double / Twin
elements.title: Art Hotel

maps.searchPlace: 30 King Faysal Street Downtown Amman، Amman, Jordan

elements.additionalText:
Located in Downtown Amman, Art Hotel features simply furnished accommodations. Free WiFi is available in all areas. The Roman Amphitheater is a 10-minute walk away.
Each room here will provide you with a flat-screen TV and air conditioning. The private bathroom also comes with a shower.
Al Khaldi Hospital is 1.7 mi and Queen Alia International Airport is 45 minutes away by car.
This is our guests' favorite part of Amman, according to independent reviews.
This property also has one of the top-rated locations in Amman! Guests are happier about it compared to other properties in the area.

segments.title: Madaba – Mount Nebo – Dead Sea – Karak – Dana Nature Reserve – Petra
segments.content:
After breakfast, you can go for a walk around Madaba. Visit the mosaics at St George's Church and the church floors at the archaeological park – before heading onto Mt Nebo, the site where Moses was buried. Your driver will take you to the viewpoint where you can see (depending on the weather) the Promised Land. Then, your driver will take you down to the Dead Sea for a swim in this extremely salty lake, and to have lunch. 

You will continue to the Dead Sea Highway and then turn up into the mountains, and your next stop is at Karak Castle, one of the largest crusader castles in the Middle East. After a break for lunch, you will continue south along the King’s Highway, an ancient trade route, which winds through the mountains and small towns, along the way stopping briefly at Dana Nature Reserve for the views over the Great Rift Valley. Your overnight stay is in Petra.

elements.subTitle: Double
elements.title: La Maison Hotel
elements.additionalText:
La Maison Hotel is uniquely located in Wadi Musa, a 5-minute walk from the Jordanian world wonder, the Red Rose City of Petra.

Hotel La Maison offers air-conditioned guest rooms with satellite TVs. The hotel has its own Lobby Lounge called The Basha. Guests can enjoy a meal or drink here anytime during the day.

This property also has one of the best-rated locations in Wadi Musa! Guests are happier about it compared to other properties in the area.

Groups particularly like the location — they rated it 9.6 for stays with multiple people.

segments.title: Petra – Wadi Rum
segments.content: Today you have a full day to visit world heritage and UNESCO site Petra. Walk through the mystic Siq, with its carvings and temples along the way. You will find the impressive Treasury at the end of the canyon and then the rest of this enormous city opens up – climb up to the High Place of Sacrifice or the largest temple – the monastery, explore the Roman theater and colonnaded street. At the end of the day, you will be transferred south down to the beautiful Wadi Rum desert, where you will spend the night under the stars at a Bedouin camp, dinner is included.

elements.subTitle: Double VIP Tent
elements.title: Khaleds Camp
elements.additionalText:
Khaled's camp is located in the middle of the Protected Area. It takes about 30- 40 minutes by 4WD to his authentic camp. In the evening you will enjoy a traditional Zarb dinner, that's prepared under the ground. 

You'll sleep in your private Bedouin Tent where you'll have a simple bed and fresh blankets. Sanitary facilities are limited in the desert and are shared. The water is heated by the sun. 

Optional upgrade: If you prefer your own toilet and shower, opt for a deluxe tent which has a little extra facilities compared to the standard tents.

segments.title: Wadi Rum - QAIA
segments.content: After breakfast, you have a jeep safari to explore the beauty of the desert – visit the Nabatean inscriptions, canyons, sand-dunes and Lawrence of Arabia’s House. Then it’s time for your transfer back north to the airport, for your flight home.
